# Project Rules for Scout Agent

## Strands SDK Requirements

- **ALWAYS use the Strands Agents SDK** for all agent implementations in this project
- **Reference the official Strands documentation** as the source of truth: https://strandsagents.com/latest/documentation/docs/
- Use the **most current methods and syntax** from the Strands SDK documentation
- The documentation is updated regularly - always check the latest patterns and best practices

## Strands SDK Patterns

### Agent Creation
- Use `from strands import Agent` for agent creation
- Use `from strands.models import BedrockModel` for model configuration
- Use `from strands.tools.mcp import MCPClient` for MCP tool integration

### Model Configuration
- Use `BedrockModel` with appropriate parameters (region_name, model_id, guardrail_id, etc.)
- Follow the current Bedrock model configuration patterns from the documentation

### Tool Integration
- Use `MCPClient` for connecting to MCP-based tools (like AgentCore Gateway)
- Follow the MCP client patterns shown in the documentation

### Code Style
- Follow async/await patterns when using MCP clients
- Use proper resource cleanup (context managers, __exit__ methods)
- Maintain consistency with existing agent implementations (portal_agent.py, kwikie_agent.py)

## Documentation Reference
- Primary source: https://strandsagents.com/latest/documentation/docs/
- When implementing new features or patterns, verify against the latest documentation
- Prefer documented patterns over custom implementations
